body:
@Riot...

I almost died laughing at your bullshit, was really a.... riot.

&quot;Yasuo belongs to the class we&rsquo;ve been calling Slayers, known informally as &lsquo;melee carries.&rsquo; These champions (like Riven or Fiora) are nimble yet squishy duelists with the damage to slay anyone, provided they make proper use of their windowed defensive tools (like Wind Wall or Riposte) to survive. By contrast, Fighters (like Vi or Darius) can take a moderate beating as they dish out their own damage, but lack the agility of a Slayer. But what happens if a Slayer gains the tankiness of a Fighter?&quot;

lolol Yasuo is actually a fighter/assassin. Not a slayer. It&#039;s even under his character bio, that is first trait is a fighter, and has been since release, but ignoring that, Darius nor Vi do damage? lol What fucking world are you living in Riot. lol Darius takes a beating, but does noooo damage.....right. Okayyyyyyyy.  {{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}} 

Darius alone does more damage then all of these &quot;Slayers&quot; put together. That and build with {{item:3044}}  and {{item:3742}}  and{{item:3047}}  on him and he is much more mobile and tankier than them all. Darius does no damage....Fucking OKAY Riot. 

&quot;Tank Yasuo happens. While lacking the explosive offense of a crit build.&quot;

Maybe stop nerfing {{item:3087}}  and {{item:3031}}  because of you break adc and let Yasuo keep his core build so he doesn&#039;t have to build tank. Or maybe actually put affective tenacity in the game so he doesn&#039;t need to build tanky so he isn&#039;t one shot late game by actually broken champions. Or even possibly stop breaking items and making Yasuo Pay for your mistakes.

&quot;Tank Yasuo&#039;s damage and mobility remain above average due to his kit, while his items grant him the durability he normally lacks.&quot;
We&rsquo;re looking to break up the trifecta and force Yasuo to commit to just a few strengths (instead of all of them). Defensive builds will retain their stickiness, but see a sharp drop in damage. We&rsquo;re happy when players adapt their styles to the needs of the game, but when Yasuo (like Ekko and Fizz before him) can cover his weaknesses without making tradeoffs, it&rsquo;s not a fair experience for anyone.&quot;

OHHhhh lets take about fair. Lets fucking talk about it. Where the fuck was this &quot;fair experience&quot; when Yasuo had the lowest win rate in game. Where was it when he was literally banned because people playing him fed to hard. Where was this when he was crap for season after season. Where was this &quot;fair&quot; when Yasuo was shat on after the adc update, or the juggernaut update, or the mage update? Fucking fair....Okaaaaaaay Riot. 

Maybe don&#039;t break items and call champions broken because of your mistakes. OR nerf core builds and hope no one fking cares. Fucking Riot.
